WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:02:08.170 --> 00:02:10.106
Another crossing burned.

3
00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:11.632
We might never reach Tumbleton.

4
00:02:12.591 --> 00:02:15.010
So how long will it take you
to build the bloody thing again?

5
00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:18.364
We will have to find another crossing.

6
00:02:18.388 --> 00:02:20.974
-take the long way round.
-The queen will abhor this delay.

7
00:02:22.559 --> 00:02:24.662
Lord Piper. take 100
of your fastest riders

8
00:02:24.686 --> 00:02:26.122
and make for Stoney Sept.

9
00:02:26.146 --> 00:02:27.606
Secure the barge and transit there.

10
00:02:29.399 --> 00:02:31.961
That puts us back by a week.
but we can do no better.

11
00:02:31.985 --> 00:02:35.530
It's our last chance to ford the river
with an army of this size.

12
00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:47.143
Will we continue to suffer this Cole

13
00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:49.646
and his band of hangers-on?

14
00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:52.774
They flit about us
like fucking deer flies.

15
00:02:52.798 --> 00:02:55.818
another thing that
we do not endure in the North.

16
00:02:55.842 --> 00:02:57.552
Better deer flies than frostbite.

17
00:02:58.762 --> 00:03:02.784
But Criston Cole I am past enduring.
North or South.

18
00:03:02.808 --> 00:03:08.397
Then loose my wolves and me on the hunt.
and we will bring him down.

19
00:03:09.815 --> 00:03:11.400
Or we could play at his game.

20
00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:49.312
Ambush!

21
00:03:54.943 --> 00:03:56.486
We're under attack!

22
00:04:00.741 --> 00:04:02.176
To the next crossing. then?

23
00:04:02.200 --> 00:04:05.763
They'll make for Stoney Sept
and we'll once more be ahead of them.

24
00:04:05.787 --> 00:04:07.164
Fall back!

25
00:04:44.284 --> 00:04:46.429
If I'd have known
we were expecting guests.

26
00:04:46.453 --> 00:04:48.181
I would have made up the beds.

27
00:04:48.205 --> 00:04:49.807
We're looking for Aemond Targaryen.

28
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:52.268
-the Kinslayer.
-Ah. yes. There's been a horde of you

29
00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:55.962
since the ungrateful queen
announced her bounty.

30
00:04:56.797 --> 00:04:59.400
Well. you won't find your quarry here.

31
00:04:59.424 --> 00:05:04.137
There's an old man who churns the butter.
but he's blind in both eyes.

32
00:05:05.180 --> 00:05:07.224
And the boy who feeds the horses.

33
00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:10.745
And then there are the ghosts.

34
00:05:10.769 --> 00:05:14.123
Seems you have not learned
the history of this place

35
00:05:14.147 --> 00:05:16.191
and the laborers who built it...

36
00:05:18.026 --> 00:05:20.862
who died here in chains...

37
00:05:21.822 --> 00:05:23.406
in service to Harren the Cruel.

38
00:05:28.578 --> 00:05:30.163
This castle breathes.

39
00:05:35.627 --> 00:05:39.214
She swallows the greedy. the heedless.

40
00:05:42.509 --> 00:05:45.971
Her founding stones were watered
with the blood of men.

41
00:05:48.014 --> 00:05:49.975
And she's always thirsty.

42
00:06:08.577 --> 00:06:10.078
Oi! You bloody craven?!

43
00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:13.832
Fuck this place.

44
00:06:29.222 --> 00:06:30.682
Can you hear me?

45
00:06:32.767 --> 00:06:34.394
Stay back! Stay back!

46
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:39.083
My brother. Aegon. he was here.

47
00:06:39.107 --> 00:06:40.859
His face was on fire.

48
00:06:41.735 --> 00:06:46.215
I saw him. He was clutching at me.
dragging me down into the dark.

49
00:06:46.239 --> 00:06:49.159
-My brother.
-It's just the dream again. That's all.

50
00:06:54.581 --> 00:06:56.875
It's just the dream again.

51
00:07:05.884 --> 00:07:07.052
She saw it.

52
00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:12.074
She said I would die.
that I ruined everything.

53
00:07:12.098 --> 00:07:13.308
No.

54
00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:24.819
Mother.

55
00:07:55.517 --> 00:07:57.745
None may enter.
save at our queen's direction.

56
00:07:57.769 --> 00:08:00.939
It is a matter of some delicacy.

57
00:08:02.565 --> 00:08:06.111
I'm not certain how familiar you are
with disorders of the...

58
00:08:07.195 --> 00:08:09.590
female persuasion.

59
00:08:09.614 --> 00:08:10.699
Hm?

60
00:08:24.295 --> 00:08:28.109
I must thank you again
for your loyalty. Grand Maester.

61
00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:30.236
I flatter myself to think
that I have ever been

62
00:08:30.260 --> 00:08:32.137
a faithful servant to Your Grace.

63
00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:35.390
More than that. you've been a friend.

64
00:08:37.600 --> 00:08:39.227
But we have now a new queen.

65
00:08:41.146 --> 00:08:44.917
And I find myself under some scrutiny.

66
00:08:44.941 --> 00:08:50.131
I fear I can no longer offer you
assistance after today

67
00:08:50.155 --> 00:08:52.365
without making the proper disclosures.

68
00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:55.493
I understand.

69
00:09:10.175 --> 00:09:11.676
I don't want it.

70
00:09:12.802 --> 00:09:13.887
You must.

71
00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:17.283
It could be a boy. Do you see?

72
00:09:17.307 --> 00:09:19.184
Aegon's heir. a rival to Joffrey.

73
00:09:20.143 --> 00:09:21.686
To Rhaenyra herself.

74
00:09:26.858 --> 00:09:29.069
She will kill it. She will have no choice.

75
00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:32.173
Or if she does not.
she will take it from you.

76
00:09:32.197 --> 00:09:34.592
Aemond still lives. as far as we know.

77
00:09:34.616 --> 00:09:35.885
He's at Harrenhal.

78
00:09:35.909 --> 00:09:37.636
No. he was there. but he has fled.

79
00:09:37.660 --> 00:09:39.829
-He's vanished.
-I have seen him.

80
00:09:41.122 --> 00:09:44.250
He burns. but without fire.

81
00:09:50.381 --> 00:09:55.095
If Aemond threatens Rhaenyra's rule.
she will use the child as her shield.

82
00:09:56.513 --> 00:09:58.866
I can't do it.

83
00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:00.725
Helaena. please. Please.

84
00:10:01.851 --> 00:10:03.812
For your own sake.
do you not wish to be free?

85
00:10:04.813 --> 00:10:06.064
I can't.

86
00:10:07.565 --> 00:10:10.086
-No. No.
-Think of it. think of it as a cup of tea.

87
00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:11.712
Nothing more.

88
00:10:11.736 --> 00:10:13.380
But it isn't.

89
00:10:13.404 --> 00:10:17.009
No. No. it's not. Listen to me.
Listen to me. it is a blessing.

90
00:10:17.033 --> 00:10:19.953
It is a remedy taught
to the masters of the Citadel.

91
00:10:20.954 --> 00:10:23.557
It has delivered me
from disgrace and ruin.

92
00:10:23.581 --> 00:10:26.060
It has delivered Rhaenyra herself
when she was young.

93
00:10:26.084 --> 00:10:27.669
And it will deliver you. too.

94
00:10:29.587 --> 00:10:30.981
-Helaena. Please. please.
-No.

95
00:10:31.005 --> 00:10:33.025
Listen to me.

96
00:10:33.049 --> 00:10:34.777
Will you bear a child

97
00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:38.072
who will be never more
than a hostage or a pawn?

98
00:10:38.096 --> 00:10:39.264
It's mine!

99
00:10:40.390 --> 00:10:42.350
It's my own. it's mine!

100
00:10:48.731 --> 00:10:50.835
I had hoped a seat on the council
would suffice

101
00:10:50.859 --> 00:10:52.920
as recompense for House Frey's loyalty.

102
00:10:52.944 --> 00:10:57.258
But Harrenhal was to be our recompense.
payment for giving your Winter Wolves

103
00:10:57.282 --> 00:11:00.052
passage across the Twins.
promised by your own son.

104
00:11:00.076 --> 00:11:02.471
-My son is dead.
-And now. I discover

105
00:11:02.495 --> 00:11:05.182
that you have pledged
our castle as a trophy.

106
00:11:05.206 --> 00:11:07.393
free to any hedge knight
who can bring you the head

107
00:11:07.417 --> 00:11:09.979
-of Aemond Targaryen.
-You. yourself. are welcome to try.

108
00:11:10.003 --> 00:11:12.648
Cregan Stark's army
has crossed the Trident.

109
00:11:12.672 --> 00:11:15.901
and we expect the crown's
word to be honored.

110
00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:18.612
no matter if some grubby sell sword

111
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:21.389
has dubbed himself Lord of Harrenhal
in the meanwhile.

112
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:28.372
For now. however.

113
00:11:28.396 --> 00:11:31.065
I would be pleased
to join Your Grace's council.

114
00:11:37.238 --> 00:11:39.758
<i>What could anyone possibly
want in Wendish Town?</i>

115
00:11:39.782 --> 00:11:44.263
Not Wendish Town itself. Your Grace.
but a small village at the outskirts.

116
00:11:44.287 --> 00:11:45.973
There were several farms burned.

117
00:11:45.997 --> 00:11:48.559
and the men we talked to were
certain it was Vhagar herself.

118
00:11:48.583 --> 00:11:51.020
The Sea Snake's bastard.
now a dragon rider.

119
00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:52.897
-That's his brother.
-Lord Darry is our ally.

120
00:11:52.921 --> 00:11:55.232
Aemond may be provoking us.

121
00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:57.568
By sacking a farm or three? To what end?

122
00:11:57.592 --> 00:11:59.069
Dragons need to eat.

123
00:11:59.093 --> 00:12:00.654
The White Worm. she was called.

124
00:12:00.678 --> 00:12:03.073
But they are fugitives.
We will root them out soon enough.

125
00:12:03.097 --> 00:12:05.099
-The whore.
-Mm-hmm.

126
00:12:10.230 --> 00:12:12.625
There was a skirmish last night
at the Dragon Gate.

127
00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:14.251
Horses were required to dispel it.

128
00:12:14.275 --> 00:12:15.794
If only the Lady Mysaria had been there

129
00:12:15.818 --> 00:12:17.838
with her promised bread
and ladlefuls of stew.

130
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:20.633
Or if. by some miracle.
the king consort's City Watch

131
00:12:20.657 --> 00:12:24.762
had shown a penny's worth of restraint
pursuing the pettiest of crimes.

132
00:12:24.786 --> 00:12:27.431
-the pettiest of criminals...
-Did anyone see where Vhagar flew?

133
00:12:27.455 --> 00:12:29.266
We went with all speed
to take up the trail.

134
00:12:29.290 --> 00:12:30.726
but it was two days cold.

135
00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:32.603
Once again. Aemond is nowhere to be found.

136
00:12:32.627 --> 00:12:36.357
Two of our gold cloaks were found dead
in the street this morning.

137
00:12:36.381 --> 00:12:38.484
Put to the blade by an unknown hand.

138
00:12:38.508 --> 00:12:39.652
Where was this?

139
00:12:39.676 --> 00:12:41.987
-Flea Bottom.
-Flea Bottom.

140
00:12:42.011 --> 00:12:44.031
Mm. has ever been a realm unto itself.

141
00:12:44.055 --> 00:12:47.910
Quite ungovernable. full of undesirables.

142
00:12:47.934 --> 00:12:51.205
Vhagar appears while Ormund Hightower

143
00:12:51.229 --> 00:12:53.290
gathers himself at Tumbleton
to some hidden purpose.

144
00:12:53.314 --> 00:12:55.417
We need not waste our sweat
fretting over a fox

145
00:12:55.441 --> 00:12:57.169
gone to ground.
If you will not burn him...

146
00:12:57.193 --> 00:12:58.671
-He is not a f...
-then my army

147
00:12:58.695 --> 00:13:00.089
will root him out soon enough.

148
00:13:00.113 --> 00:13:02.007
As to that. there is fresh news

149
00:13:02.031 --> 00:13:04.260
from Lord Tully's camp.

150
00:13:04.284 --> 00:13:06.220
Their march has been slowed
by interference

151
00:13:06.244 --> 00:13:08.430
from Ser Criston Cole and his men.

152
00:13:08.454 --> 00:13:11.684
River crossings are being burned
before the army can reach them.

153
00:13:11.708 --> 00:13:13.310
Go back to the Riverlands.

154
00:13:13.334 --> 00:13:15.437
If Aemond has shown himself once.
he may do so again.

155
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:18.232
Take no risk. but ascertain his path.
his purpose.

156
00:13:18.256 --> 00:13:19.692
If I may. Your Grace.

157
00:13:19.716 --> 00:13:22.820
We arrived back only this morning.

158
00:13:22.844 --> 00:13:25.072
The Lady Baela has not eaten.
much less slept.

159
00:13:25.096 --> 00:13:26.907
I am more than ready to fly.

160
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:28.534
It will not serve us
if your eyes are weary

161
00:13:28.558 --> 00:13:30.452
and your beast fatigued.

162
00:13:30.476 --> 00:13:31.936
I will send Daemon.

163
00:13:33.187 --> 00:13:36.542
I will go once I have dealt
with this business in the city.

164
00:13:36.566 --> 00:13:38.794
Our fallen soldiers.
An accounting must be made.

165
00:13:38.818 --> 00:13:41.255
-Do you not agree?
-I am able. Your Grace.

166
00:13:41.279 --> 00:13:42.965
The loss to our City Watch

167
00:13:42.989 --> 00:13:45.783
is a crime. to be sure.
but Ser Luthor will investigate.

168
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:49.263
-It is not a matter for the crown.
-They are my men.

169
00:13:49.287 --> 00:13:51.998
And we depend on those men now
to secure your rule.

170
00:13:54.292 --> 00:13:56.544
Especially since their wages
have been withheld.

171
00:14:00.048 --> 00:14:01.549
-Your Grace.
-Not now.

172
00:14:02.925 --> 00:14:04.344
Is it always like this?

173
00:14:05.136 --> 00:14:06.697
Mm.

174
00:14:06.721 --> 00:14:07.972
Daemon.

175
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:12.494
Have I somehow found myself
back on Dragonstone?

176
00:14:12.518 --> 00:14:14.955
That my voice must again
compete with yours?

177
00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:17.166
On the contrary. I have pledged
to fulfill your command.

178
00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:18.083
Just...

179
00:14:18.107 --> 00:14:19.001
later.

180
00:14:19.025 --> 00:14:21.337
I'm in no mood to jest.
What does it make of me

181
00:14:21.361 --> 00:14:23.672
if you will obey me only at a time
and place of your own choosing?

182
00:14:23.696 --> 00:14:25.424
You are the queen.

183
00:14:25.448 --> 00:14:27.301
I act in your interest.

184
00:14:27.325 --> 00:14:30.095
Good. My interest is Vhagar.

185
00:14:30.119 --> 00:14:31.680
Mine too. But we have time enough.

186
00:14:31.704 --> 00:14:34.850
Aemond is afraid.
He has fled once already before you.

187
00:14:34.874 --> 00:14:37.770
-We are in no danger.
-There is treachery somewhere.

188
00:14:37.794 --> 00:14:39.480
and I seek to uncover it.

189
00:14:39.504 --> 00:14:41.815
What you seek is revenge.

190
00:14:41.839 --> 00:14:45.277
And gods know I do not grudge you that.
but revenge may wait.

191
00:14:45.301 --> 00:14:47.571
At this moment. there is
a disturbance in your city.

192
00:14:47.595 --> 00:14:49.806
and you. yourself. are its likely cause.

193
00:14:52.266 --> 00:14:54.703
I did not ask Ser Luthor to be brutal.

194
00:14:54.727 --> 00:14:57.414
You need not have
asked him anything at all.

195
00:14:57.438 --> 00:14:59.875
Will you let yourself
be rattled by vapid taunts.

196
00:14:59.899 --> 00:15:01.710
by the painting of stripes
on tavern walls?

197
00:15:01.734 --> 00:15:04.755
They are more than taunts.
They are an insult to my sons.

198
00:15:04.779 --> 00:15:06.757
A challenge to my very legitimacy.

199
00:15:06.781 --> 00:15:08.675
You are the Queen of Dragons.

200
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:10.803
Your strength is your legitimacy.

201
00:15:10.827 --> 00:15:12.078
Your Grace?

202
00:15:18.668 --> 00:15:20.044
Glad news.

203
00:15:20.711 --> 00:15:23.548
Young Prince Joffrey
has returned this hour from the Vale.

204
00:15:26.467 --> 00:15:28.719
I'm told he's asked for you.

205
00:15:30.388 --> 00:15:34.809
I will come to him when I'm able.
I'm sure he's tired.

206
00:15:40.481 --> 00:15:42.167
It is long past the nightingale.

207
00:15:42.191 --> 00:15:44.086
I don't care.

208
00:15:44.110 --> 00:15:45.570
Which way is West?

209
00:15:46.529 --> 00:15:47.655
I have no idea.

210
00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:55.681
-If I may say. Your Grace...
-I'm not going back.

211
00:15:55.705 --> 00:15:58.392
-We have nowhere else to go.
-You heard what I did.

212
00:15:58.416 --> 00:16:00.519
Vhagar has been sighted at Wendish Town.

213
00:16:00.543 --> 00:16:02.563
Two days ago.
Who knows where she may be now?

214
00:16:02.587 --> 00:16:05.190
Well. Harrenhal. then.
Someone there will know something.

215
00:16:05.214 --> 00:16:07.526
Look. Aemond must have left
a message or a sign.

216
00:16:07.550 --> 00:16:09.695
-We can pick up his trail.
-It's 100 leagues

217
00:16:09.719 --> 00:16:11.238
to Harrenhal. Your Grace. and the fields

218
00:16:11.262 --> 00:16:13.574
and woods are teeming with Rivermen.

219
00:16:13.598 --> 00:16:16.452
This is more than a folly.
It is dangerous.

220
00:16:16.476 --> 00:16:19.479
Fucking seven fucking hells!

221
00:16:21.147 --> 00:16:23.750
What would you do if you found him. hm?

222
00:16:23.774 --> 00:16:27.588
Your brother is a coiled viper.
and you are...

223
00:16:27.612 --> 00:16:31.633
you are hungry. and broken.
and spent. and we are alone.

224
00:16:31.657 --> 00:16:33.051
If we were to be discovered...

225
00:16:33.075 --> 00:16:35.244
Stop telling me what I can't do!

226
00:16:38.581 --> 00:16:39.999
This is his fault.

227
00:16:41.209 --> 00:16:42.210
Everything.

228
00:16:43.294 --> 00:16:48.233
Every one of my miseries is of his making.
and I swear before the Warrior himself.

229
00:16:48.257 --> 00:16:52.720
I'm going to find him and fucking kill him
or die in the attempt.

230
00:16:53.930 --> 00:16:54.931
Hm.

231
00:17:18.496 --> 00:17:19.997
You know me. I think.

232
00:17:22.291 --> 00:17:23.477
By reputation.

233
00:17:23.501 --> 00:17:28.649
It is my privilege now to listen
to the whispers of the Red Keep.

234
00:17:28.673 --> 00:17:31.026
-The guests you receive...
-What is it that you want?

235
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:33.844
And the gifts they bring.

236
00:17:35.763 --> 00:17:37.223
Show it to me.

237
00:17:53.322 --> 00:17:55.092
My daughter has been unwell.

238
00:17:55.116 --> 00:17:57.511
As you see. she suffers
terrible headaches.

239
00:17:57.535 --> 00:18:01.056
The maester is kind enough to tend to her.

240
00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:03.332
And yet the flask is full.

241
00:18:08.629 --> 00:18:10.840
I took a lover after Viserys.

242
00:18:11.841 --> 00:18:15.428
The queen herself knows the truth of it.
I was careless. to my shame.

243
00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:21.934
It's a difficult thing.
but I should no longer delay.

244
00:18:33.988 --> 00:18:37.134
Was he a lord or a commoner?

245
00:18:37.158 --> 00:18:38.993
Or perhaps both?

246
00:18:41.912 --> 00:18:44.498
I must appeal to you. Lady Mysaria.

247
00:18:46.250 --> 00:18:48.419
You of all people must understand the...

248
00:18:49.545 --> 00:18:52.423
the indignities we women endure.

249
00:18:54.467 --> 00:18:56.653
There is surely no need for this
to be spoken of again.

250
00:18:56.677 --> 00:18:59.639
You would not. of course.
seek to deceive the queen.

251
00:19:02.266 --> 00:19:04.143
I am her prisoner.

252
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:08.189
As you were once. if I'm not mistaken.

253
00:19:14.987 --> 00:19:16.739
As you say.

254
00:19:23.537 --> 00:19:24.973
Have you ever seen the Hightower

255
00:19:24.997 --> 00:19:26.457
at Oldtown. Ser Criston?

256
00:19:27.416 --> 00:19:28.626
I've heard tell of it.

257
00:19:29.794 --> 00:19:31.796
Ormund and I had a game.

258
00:19:32.588 --> 00:19:33.923
to "run the tower."

259
00:19:35.216 --> 00:19:37.152
You'd start at the base before dawn

260
00:19:37.176 --> 00:19:39.488
and aim to be the first one
to see the sun rise

261
00:19:39.512 --> 00:19:41.073
from the beacon.

262
00:19:41.097 --> 00:19:42.932
Of course. I let him win.

263
00:19:43.974 --> 00:19:45.768
He was a thin-skinned twat even then.

264
00:19:46.769 --> 00:19:48.664
Mm.

265
00:19:48.688 --> 00:19:54.044
At that moment. when the sun rises
over the Seven Kingdoms.

266
00:19:54.068 --> 00:19:55.986
hundreds and hundreds of miles...

267
00:19:57.697 --> 00:19:59.990
I hope to show it to you one day.

268
00:20:01.701 --> 00:20:03.929
You could make a home
at Oldtown. Ser Criston.

269
00:20:03.953 --> 00:20:06.747
A knight of your stature
would be most welcome...

270
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:10.167
to serve our house there.

271
00:20:16.674 --> 00:20:18.592
Halt! Stay back!

272
00:20:23.889 --> 00:20:25.599
Stay clear!

273
00:20:28.436 --> 00:20:29.770
Hold your ground!

274
00:20:31.147 --> 00:20:32.523
Stand your ground!

275
00:20:42.408 --> 00:20:44.577
Crow's feet.

276
00:20:45.786 --> 00:20:47.013
Gods.

277
00:20:47.037 --> 00:20:48.789
Are they ahead of us?

278
00:21:40.549 --> 00:21:43.236
<i>Your hand was heavier
than warranted by the crime.</i>

279
00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:46.406
I was well schooled
in those manners. was I not?

280
00:21:46.430 --> 00:21:48.098
I had the finest of captains.

281
00:21:49.642 --> 00:21:52.454
In any case. the queen wanted it stopped.

282
00:21:52.478 --> 00:21:55.081
The queen's son is dead.
She must be excused her impulses.

283
00:21:55.105 --> 00:21:58.210
-Oh. you'd have me refuse her?
-No. rather temper her.

284
00:21:58.234 --> 00:21:59.211
Tend to her humors.

285
00:21:59.235 --> 00:22:01.838
Not every whim needs to be
pursued with equal vigor.

286
00:22:01.862 --> 00:22:04.674
You know. they cut their bowels
as well as their throat.

287
00:22:04.698 --> 00:22:06.259
Did they tell you that?

288
00:22:06.283 --> 00:22:09.411
Good men dying in agony in their own shit.

289
00:22:10.412 --> 00:22:12.015
We will pay the villains back in kind.

290
00:22:12.039 --> 00:22:13.934
What is the mood among the men?

291
00:22:13.958 --> 00:22:15.894
They complain about their wages.
or lack of them.

292
00:22:15.918 --> 00:22:17.395
I shall address them.

293
00:22:17.419 --> 00:22:19.898
A rousing speech from
the Rogue Prince himself.

294
00:22:19.922 --> 00:22:22.192
I'm not sure that's gonna make up
for a steady wage anymore.

295
00:22:22.216 --> 00:22:24.110
If I lead them. they will follow.

296
00:22:24.134 --> 00:22:26.154
It's been a minute

297
00:22:26.178 --> 00:22:28.448
since you were the Prince of Flea Bottom.

298
00:22:28.472 --> 00:22:31.767
Most of the men were in
swaddling clothes when you...

299
00:23:32.703 --> 00:23:34.097
What is our standing?

300
00:23:34.121 --> 00:23:36.433
Battlements are being raised
with haste. my lord.

301
00:23:36.457 --> 00:23:40.896
But we lack in timber. and men. and time.

302
00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:43.023
Then levy more conscripts.

303
00:23:43.047 --> 00:23:45.650
and fell every tree
from here to Bitter bridge.

304
00:23:45.674 --> 00:23:47.277
We must secure our walls.

305
00:23:47.301 --> 00:23:48.928
Rhaenyra's host is surely on the march.

306
00:23:50.304 --> 00:23:53.432
The maester tells me you've been
most assiduous in your lessons.

307
00:23:55.309 --> 00:23:57.495
We are making a study on my forebears

308
00:23:57.519 --> 00:23:59.289
on the Hightower side.

309
00:23:59.313 --> 00:24:02.876
I mean. their battles. their enemies.

310
00:24:02.900 --> 00:24:04.920
It has been three days
now spent in the pursuit

311
00:24:04.944 --> 00:24:06.320
of these dry histories.

312
00:24:09.782 --> 00:24:11.325
Dry. did you say?

313
00:24:13.786 --> 00:24:15.537
No. Of course not.

314
00:24:18.415 --> 00:24:21.227
Or rather. they may
seem dry at first glance.

315
00:24:21.251 --> 00:24:22.795
but to learn fr...

316
00:24:24.088 --> 00:24:28.818
To venerate our ancestors.
that is a noble task.

317
00:24:28.842 --> 00:24:30.469
And I'm grateful for it.

318
00:24:31.720 --> 00:24:33.323
Good.

319
00:24:33.347 --> 00:24:35.516
It would please me to hear you recite.

320
00:24:39.687 --> 00:24:42.165
We have parsed out the conflicts

321
00:24:42.189 --> 00:24:46.836
between House Greyjoy and Houses Peake

322
00:24:46.860 --> 00:24:48.922
and Osgrey and Gardener.

323
00:24:48.946 --> 00:24:50.131
House Dayne of Dorne...

324
00:24:50.155 --> 00:24:51.699
And Meria Martell?

325
00:24:53.492 --> 00:24:55.494
The Yellow Toad of Dorne.

326
00:24:58.831 --> 00:25:00.666
I should have a word with your tutor.

327
00:25:02.292 --> 00:25:04.604
She was the only woman ever
to have been gifted

328
00:25:04.628 --> 00:25:07.006
with a truly military mind.

329
00:25:09.174 --> 00:25:12.261
Though the gods divested her
of beauty in turn.

330
00:25:13.095 --> 00:25:14.656
A blind princess.

331
00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:17.766
Hideous. hairless. thick of waist.

332
00:25:19.393 --> 00:25:21.729
She does not sound so formidable.

333
00:25:24.314 --> 00:25:26.334
When Aegon the Conqueror
claimed her lands.

334
00:25:26.358 --> 00:25:27.693
she refused to submit.

335
00:25:29.028 --> 00:25:30.964
She declared him a usurper.

336
00:25:30.988 --> 00:25:32.507
And all those that marched for him.

337
00:25:32.531 --> 00:25:33.991
traitors to the Seven Kingdoms.

338
00:25:35.367 --> 00:25:40.372
And she swore that Dorne
would ever be unbowed. unbent.

339
00:25:47.046 --> 00:25:50.191
A great host descended
from the Red Mountains.

340
00:25:50.215 --> 00:25:52.569
we Hightowers regrettably among them.

341
00:25:52.593 --> 00:25:54.487
Meria poisoned her own wells.

342
00:25:54.511 --> 00:25:57.264
hid her soldiers
in the very sand of the desert.

343
00:25:58.390 --> 00:26:00.452
Her castle. when they found it. was empty.

344
00:26:00.476 --> 00:26:02.996
They thought that she was vanquished.

345
00:26:03.020 --> 00:26:07.066
But she rose up out of the darkness
and slaughtered them in their beds.

346
00:26:09.276 --> 00:26:12.404
Is she a hero. then? Or a villain?

347
00:26:19.286 --> 00:26:22.849
The Targaryens knew
nothing of our civilization.

348
00:26:22.873 --> 00:26:24.434
the Faith. the Citadel.

349
00:26:24.458 --> 00:26:26.269
What they had.

350
00:26:26.293 --> 00:26:29.755
what they still have. is strength.

351
00:26:31.090 --> 00:26:33.425
Their armies.
the obscenity of their dragons.

352
00:26:34.259 --> 00:26:36.845
Meria Martell outwitted her enemy.

353
00:26:37.805 --> 00:26:41.975
A cunning mind can resist
the most savage of beasts.

354
00:26:43.393 --> 00:26:46.939
And Dorne remains unbroken even today.

355
00:27:04.832 --> 00:27:05.999
I was lucky.

356
00:27:08.210 --> 00:27:09.461
Let us start again.

357
00:27:32.317 --> 00:27:34.736
Never apologize for victory.

358
00:27:43.912 --> 00:27:45.497
I have had these made.

359
00:27:56.091 --> 00:27:57.467
Do you think it a good likeness?

360
00:28:00.137 --> 00:28:04.033
You are the sign our allies
have been waiting for.

361
00:28:04.057 --> 00:28:07.936
The son of Viserys.
the beacon shining from the High Tower.

362
00:28:09.313 --> 00:28:13.066
From the lowliest of the faithful
to Borros Baratheon himself.

363
00:28:19.907 --> 00:28:22.326
Oh. No. you can't touch that.

364
00:28:23.577 --> 00:28:24.786
Helaena?

365
00:28:27.122 --> 00:28:28.290
Do you know why?

366
00:28:29.291 --> 00:28:33.188
They eat the leaves of the nightshade.
but that would be death for you or me.

367
00:28:33.212 --> 00:28:34.480
It's a puzzle.

368
00:28:34.504 --> 00:28:35.923
Jaehaera. come with me.

369
00:28:41.637 --> 00:28:42.930
Come.

370
00:28:47.643 --> 00:28:49.871
Listen now. dearest. We must leave here.

371
00:28:49.895 --> 00:28:51.355
This very evening.

372
00:28:52.981 --> 00:28:54.751
There seems to be
some trouble in the city.

373
00:28:54.775 --> 00:28:58.129
and some of Rhaenyra's soldiers
must go to help the City Watch.

374
00:28:58.153 --> 00:28:59.953
We will have one guard tonight
instead of two.

375
00:29:03.951 --> 00:29:05.303
Your necklace.

376
00:29:05.327 --> 00:29:07.371
I tendered it to a maid. She will help us.

377
00:29:08.580 --> 00:29:11.333
There is a hidden door that
leads out in Aemond's chamber.

378
00:29:12.251 --> 00:29:13.794
Below the keep and beyond its walls.

379
00:29:14.711 --> 00:29:17.047
The one the men used
when they came to kill my boy?

380
00:29:19.174 --> 00:29:20.592
The room is Baela's now.

381
00:29:21.843 --> 00:29:23.595
And she will no doubt be out hunting.

382
00:29:25.555 --> 00:29:26.824
With luck. we may escape

383
00:29:26.848 --> 00:29:29.118
and melt into the streets
of King's Landing.

384
00:29:29.142 --> 00:29:30.727
And Jaehaera?

385
00:29:32.354 --> 00:29:33.939
Her room is guarded.

386
00:29:34.815 --> 00:29:37.693
If she were to cry out. even once...

387
00:29:38.944 --> 00:29:41.024
-then that would be the end.
-I will not leave her.

388
00:29:42.656 --> 00:29:45.760
The road ahead will not be safe for her.

389
00:29:45.784 --> 00:29:50.640
Here. she has nursemaids to care for her.
and Rhaenyra will not harm her.

390
00:29:50.664 --> 00:29:52.784
Her rivals would never
raise a girl up to rule. and...

391
00:29:53.959 --> 00:29:55.645
and it might be prudent.

392
00:29:55.669 --> 00:29:58.273
in fact. for the queen
to take the child to ward.

393
00:29:58.297 --> 00:30:01.675
We may even be able to...
to send for her one day.

394
00:30:08.890 --> 00:30:10.642
You look away when you lie.

395
00:30:15.439 --> 00:30:19.234
It has been days since Vhagar was here.
She feeds. then eludes us.

396
00:30:20.402 --> 00:30:23.405
We have traversed the Trident
50 times in the last fortnight.

397
00:30:24.656 --> 00:30:26.718
For now. we must rest.

398
00:30:26.742 --> 00:30:29.762
Could Aemond be crossing
into the Westerlands to hide?

399
00:30:29.786 --> 00:30:31.597
The Lannisters are allies.

400
00:30:31.621 --> 00:30:33.725
and there are caves and crannies
aplenty in those mountains.

401
00:30:33.749 --> 00:30:35.643
And I'll be pleased
to explore them with you

402
00:30:35.667 --> 00:30:37.770
when you've had a sleep and a meal.

403
00:30:37.794 --> 00:30:39.314
-He may be moving by night...
-Baela!

404
00:30:42.716 --> 00:30:44.819
-My lady.
-It is well enough for you.

405
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:48.364
The queen sees you as her talisman.
a sign from the gods. but I...

406
00:30:48.388 --> 00:30:49.741
It wasn't your fault.

407
00:30:49.765 --> 00:30:51.558
She won't look at me.

408
00:30:53.268 --> 00:30:54.895
And I cannot say I blame her.

409
00:30:57.064 --> 00:30:59.250
The truth is. Addam. I wanted to go.

410
00:30:59.274 --> 00:31:01.026
I saw myself a hero.

411
00:31:02.402 --> 00:31:04.988
Turning the tide of a great battle and...

412
00:31:06.323 --> 00:31:08.009
proving my worth to the realm.

413
00:31:08.033 --> 00:31:10.887
I have the same desire. as do others.

414
00:31:10.911 --> 00:31:13.246
It is pride. and I am punished for it.

415
00:31:15.040 --> 00:31:16.541
My future was ordained.

416
00:31:17.834 --> 00:31:19.252
I was one day to be queen.

417
00:31:20.170 --> 00:31:22.607
My path lay straight before me. and now...

418
00:31:22.631 --> 00:31:24.359
Your path has vanished.

419
00:31:24.383 --> 00:31:26.134
Though it has been replaced. perhaps.

420
00:31:27.761 --> 00:31:29.155
By an adventure.

421
00:31:29.179 --> 00:31:31.866
I'll be married off. likely enough.

422
00:31:31.890 --> 00:31:35.661
to some ancient.
self-regarding lord in Pyke.

423
00:31:35.685 --> 00:31:37.497
with enough hoarded gold
to pay Rhaenyra's debts.

424
00:31:37.521 --> 00:31:39.356
And then. I'll come and find you.

425
00:31:40.357 --> 00:31:41.733
And we'll fly to exile.

426
00:31:43.860 --> 00:31:45.445
But only if we eat first.

427
00:31:51.993 --> 00:31:53.412
Vhagar!

428
00:31:55.163 --> 00:31:56.415
She's gone.

429
00:31:58.458 --> 00:31:59.852
No.

430
00:31:59.876 --> 00:32:02.647
No. no. she will not abandon me.

431
00:32:02.671 --> 00:32:06.633
I know only that she flew in the night
and I did not see where.

432
00:32:07.717 --> 00:32:09.302
Maybe she was afraid.

433
00:32:15.350 --> 00:32:16.935
Am I a prisoner?

434
00:32:49.217 --> 00:32:50.594
No.

435
00:32:55.557 --> 00:32:57.476
Without her. I'm nothing.

436
00:32:58.643 --> 00:33:01.271
-You are mistaken.
-I must find her.

437
00:33:02.814 --> 00:33:06.234
And how will you do that
if the dragon has fled?

438
00:33:08.111 --> 00:33:09.821
The queen hunts her as well.

439
00:33:12.908 --> 00:33:14.552
The queen?

440
00:33:14.576 --> 00:33:16.870
I told you. King's Landing has fallen.

441
00:33:18.371 --> 00:33:20.499
I thought I dreamed it.

442
00:33:25.378 --> 00:33:26.505
Aegon?

443
00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:29.341
The queen says he's dead.

444
00:33:30.467 --> 00:33:31.718
And that you killed him.

445
00:33:36.181 --> 00:33:38.600
Though I do not know
how much of that to believe.

446
00:33:40.894 --> 00:33:44.397
He is dead because he will not let me be.

447
00:33:49.694 --> 00:33:50.946
He...

448
00:33:51.780 --> 00:33:53.240
he tormented me.

449
00:33:56.409 --> 00:33:57.911
My childhood...

450
00:33:58.828 --> 00:34:00.205
I worshiped him.

451
00:34:09.130 --> 00:34:10.757
And yet our mother...

452
00:34:13.843 --> 00:34:15.136
Sometimes...

453
00:34:16.471 --> 00:34:18.348
the child that grieves her...

454
00:34:19.808 --> 00:34:21.851
is the one a mother loves best.

455
00:34:23.103 --> 00:34:24.104
Hm?

456
00:34:27.983 --> 00:34:29.317
Who are you?

457
00:34:32.028 --> 00:34:33.863
One that has been grieved.

458
00:34:42.247 --> 00:34:43.373
Go on.

459
00:34:44.291 --> 00:34:45.292
Say it.

460
00:34:48.420 --> 00:34:49.838
My dragon is dead.

461
00:34:50.797 --> 00:34:52.215
I'm a pathetic cripple.

462
00:34:53.216 --> 00:34:57.738
And there is no possible scenario
in which I make it to Wendish Town

463
00:34:57.762 --> 00:34:59.740
to kill my stupid fucking brother.

464
00:34:59.764 --> 00:35:03.226
Now as you should say. should we...
should we return to the camp. Your Grace?

465
00:35:04.853 --> 00:35:07.748
I do not care to be
discovered here unguarded.

466
00:35:07.772 --> 00:35:09.166
and less so when darkness falls.

467
00:35:09.190 --> 00:35:13.236
He was Cole's little pet. do you remember?
A prodigy with the sword.

468
00:35:14.112 --> 00:35:16.448
Father withdrew me from
the tournaments. of course.

469
00:35:17.240 --> 00:35:20.678
Can't even remember the pretext anymore.

470
00:35:20.702 --> 00:35:23.347
Probably just afraid
that I'd fall off my horse.

471
00:35:23.371 --> 00:35:26.392
So. I had to sit and applaud him.

472
00:35:26.416 --> 00:35:28.251
Aemond the champion.

473
00:35:30.211 --> 00:35:32.189
And such a quick student.

474
00:35:32.213 --> 00:35:34.591
Fucking fluent in High Valyrian.

475
00:35:42.390 --> 00:35:46.311
I'm sure he thought I was a terrible king.
but what I could have been if I was...

476
00:35:47.062 --> 00:35:49.540
given his fucking advantages.

477
00:35:49.564 --> 00:35:52.418
And Mother indulged him.
She loved him more. is the truth of it.

478
00:35:52.442 --> 00:35:55.796
Poor darling Aemond
and his scabby little eye.

479
00:35:55.820 --> 00:35:58.657
And now he's killed me.
and the whole fucking realm knows it.

480
00:36:05.455 --> 00:36:07.975
-I must say. Your Grace.
-What?

481
00:36:07.999 --> 00:36:10.418
All this time we've been together...

482
00:36:12.754 --> 00:36:14.899
from the moment you were injured. in fact.

483
00:36:14.923 --> 00:36:17.759
flying drunk into a battle
to which you were not invited...

484
00:36:18.677 --> 00:36:22.305
you've done nothing but whinge

485
00:36:23.431 --> 00:36:28.371
and self-flagellate with a tenacity
I find astonishing.

486
00:36:28.395 --> 00:36:32.083
You. who had every advantage in life.

487
00:36:32.107 --> 00:36:36.128
You. who had every chance to shine.

488
00:36:36.152 --> 00:36:41.592
Firstborn son. prince of the realm.
the finest tutors. the finest knights

489
00:36:41.616 --> 00:36:43.243
instructing you in the sword.

490
00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:47.205
A dragon so beautiful.
they named him after the sun itself.

491
00:36:49.916 --> 00:36:52.752
You could have risen to greatness.

492
00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:58.174
But instead. you trampled
your birthright in the mud.

493
00:37:00.927 --> 00:37:02.220
You lazed...

494
00:37:03.430 --> 00:37:05.765
reveling in mediocrity...

495
00:37:06.933 --> 00:37:09.203
fucking anything in sight
and drinking yourself

496
00:37:09.227 --> 00:37:11.896
into oblivion with
your sycophantic friends.

497
00:37:16.317 --> 00:37:17.819
I will tell you the truth.

498
00:37:19.279 --> 00:37:20.864
You were a terrible king.

499
00:37:22.615 --> 00:37:23.950
But worse than that...

500
00:37:25.034 --> 00:37:28.705
you are a terrible man.

501
00:37:44.512 --> 00:37:45.638
Don't.

502
00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:49.184
They said you were here.

503
00:37:49.851 --> 00:37:51.328
I thought there was some mistake.

504
00:37:51.352 --> 00:37:57.126
They require of me. perhaps.
just some show of deference. or regard.

505
00:37:57.150 --> 00:37:59.110
-The people or the Seven?
-Both.

506
00:38:00.487 --> 00:38:02.989
There can be no harm in it. at the least.
You could try it.

507
00:38:17.420 --> 00:38:19.815
Four of my men lie dead.

508
00:38:19.839 --> 00:38:21.442
Six. if you count the two from yesterday.

509
00:38:21.466 --> 00:38:23.802
All gold cloaks.
all killed in the same way.

510
00:38:24.677 --> 00:38:25.845
Throats cut.

511
00:40:44.776 --> 00:40:46.194
You are tired.

512
00:40:50.073 --> 00:40:51.842
You hear the wind in these vaulted towers

513
00:40:51.866 --> 00:40:53.993
and imagine their omens
when there are none.

514
00:40:56.829 --> 00:40:58.623
Hm? These are men only.

515
00:40:59.666 --> 00:41:01.751
-Nothing more.
-Then why can't you find them?

516
00:41:30.363 --> 00:41:32.240
You are more than this.

517
00:41:36.577 --> 00:41:38.514
<i>This costs us precious time.</i>

518
00:41:38.538 --> 00:41:39.890
That is no doubt their goal.

519
00:41:39.914 --> 00:41:43.644
They knew we would leave the road
when we abandoned our mounts.

520
00:41:43.668 --> 00:41:46.814
This land may be theirs. but even
they could not cause thorns

521
00:41:46.838 --> 00:41:50.401
and brambles to spring
from the earth in our path.

522
00:41:50.425 --> 00:41:51.986
And men are talking of desertion.

523
00:41:52.010 --> 00:41:54.721
Ser Criston. Friend.

524
00:41:56.472 --> 00:41:59.368
They see no sense in continuing
with this plan and to speak truth.

525
00:41:59.392 --> 00:42:01.286
nor do I. We grow weak.

526
00:42:01.310 --> 00:42:03.604
-Stoney Sept still lies far ahead.
-Mm.

527
00:42:09.318 --> 00:42:10.945
If we leave the track here...

528
00:42:11.863 --> 00:42:13.590
cut straight through the lowlands
toward the crossing.

529
00:42:13.614 --> 00:42:15.694
we may yet still gain a day or two
over Tully's host.

530
00:42:52.528 --> 00:42:54.363
Just hire the fucking ship.

531
00:43:02.163 --> 00:43:03.790
What ship might that be?

532
00:43:05.792 --> 00:43:07.293
Seven hells.

533
00:43:16.219 --> 00:43:17.804
He's gone. My lady. be quick.

534
00:43:30.775 --> 00:43:33.837
You said the nurse
would meet us with Jaehaera.

535
00:43:33.861 --> 00:43:35.214
And so she will. at the other end.

536
00:43:35.238 --> 00:43:37.073
-Where?
-Come. now. Quickly.

537
00:43:46.916 --> 00:43:49.293
Did you imagine I wouldn't be watching?

538
00:43:52.088 --> 00:43:54.858
So it is she who is with child.

539
00:43:54.882 --> 00:43:56.693
An inconvenient heir.

540
00:43:56.717 --> 00:43:59.154
There is no need for Rhaenyra to hear
of what transpired tonight.

541
00:43:59.178 --> 00:44:02.116
I will keep no more secrets
from the queen.

542
00:44:02.140 --> 00:44:04.267
And what will be the result
if you tell her?

543
00:44:05.601 --> 00:44:07.395
We are already at her mercy.

544
00:44:08.563 --> 00:44:10.916
In but a short time. Helaena's condition
will make itself known.

545
00:44:10.940 --> 00:44:13.043
as these things cannot help but do.

546
00:44:13.067 --> 00:44:14.819
It is not for me to decide.

547
00:44:17.196 --> 00:44:19.157
I heard tell of the White Worm.

548
00:44:21.075 --> 00:44:22.075
Years ago.

549
00:44:22.743 --> 00:44:26.205
She dealt in secrets and extortion.
and I knew men who feared her.

550
00:44:28.249 --> 00:44:31.728
She had the cunning to play all sides.
not just lapdog to the queen.

551
00:44:31.752 --> 00:44:34.982
These are rich words
in the mouth of a Hightower.

552
00:44:35.006 --> 00:44:38.551
I simply urge you to think of yourself.

553
00:44:39.886 --> 00:44:42.096
There is good in Rhaenyra. but...

554
00:44:43.139 --> 00:44:45.016
the crown is a weight that crushes.

555
00:44:49.854 --> 00:44:51.707
Rhaenyra will do in the end
what she has to do.

556
00:44:51.731 --> 00:44:53.816
and what she has to do will be dire.

557
00:44:55.443 --> 00:44:57.504
There is only one who can walk
that path with her.

558
00:44:57.528 --> 00:44:58.881
and she chose him long ago.

559
00:44:58.905 --> 00:45:00.591
She knows what Daemon is.

560
00:45:00.615 --> 00:45:03.218
They have ever been two sides of a coin...

561
00:45:03.242 --> 00:45:04.744
as much as she may deny it.

562
00:45:07.663 --> 00:45:10.475
Her attentions may be on you now.

563
00:45:10.499 --> 00:45:14.253
that you bathe in the warm light
of her gaze. but...

564
00:45:15.796 --> 00:45:19.133
will you stake so high a wager
on the whims of a dragon rider?

565
00:45:20.218 --> 00:45:21.552
I want to go out.

566
00:45:23.596 --> 00:45:25.223
-Not now. dearest.
-Yes.

567
00:45:27.808 --> 00:45:29.369
I need to see the moon.

568
00:45:29.393 --> 00:45:31.145
The window will have to do.

569
00:45:32.605 --> 00:45:36.168
Speak. and you serve no one.
you gain the queen no advantage.

570
00:45:36.192 --> 00:45:39.445
But if you say nothing. no harm is done.

571
00:45:40.488 --> 00:45:42.615
You earn yourself favor
with the Hightowers...

572
00:45:45.618 --> 00:45:47.745
if a time should come
when you have need of it.

573
00:46:15.189 --> 00:46:17.358
He tried to stay awake
for you. Your Grace.

574
00:46:22.446 --> 00:46:25.092
Come on. keep moving!

575
00:46:25.116 --> 00:46:26.993
Keep moving now!

576
00:46:51.600 --> 00:46:53.269
Forward.

577
00:46:57.857 --> 00:47:00.818
Leave him! Leave him where he fell.

578
00:48:12.598 --> 00:48:13.992
Where is he?

579
00:48:14.016 --> 00:48:15.893
Aemond One-Eye. We know he's been here.

580
00:48:16.936 --> 00:48:19.063
Good ser. this has become tiresome.

581
00:48:20.231 --> 00:48:22.709
I'm of a mind to send a message
to the queen myself.

582
00:48:22.733 --> 00:48:24.252
He's not here.

583
00:48:24.276 --> 00:48:26.463
-He has never been here.
-She's lying.

584
00:48:26.487 --> 00:48:28.757
I've heard about you. witch.

585
00:48:28.781 --> 00:48:31.367
She's no witch. She's an imbecile.

586
00:48:32.118 --> 00:48:34.930
Cast out and wandering.
Touched in the head.

587
00:48:34.954 --> 00:48:36.681
Though not in the cunny
for too long. I think.

588
00:48:36.705 --> 00:48:39.893
Will you speak to me thus
in the very shadow of my fortress?

589
00:48:39.917 --> 00:48:41.770
It's been weeks since I've had a woman.

590
00:48:41.794 --> 00:48:44.255
I'm going to fuck you
and make you my salt wife.

591
00:48:58.811 --> 00:48:59.854
Ah!

592
00:49:24.712 --> 00:49:26.755
Seems you've taken a turn for the better.

593
00:49:36.891 --> 00:49:40.162
In Essos. we can secrete His Grace
until the time is right for his return.

594
00:49:40.186 --> 00:49:43.290
But we are watched now.
We can linger here no longer.

595
00:49:43.314 --> 00:49:45.667
-You risk his safety merely by speaking...
-An ocean passage beset

596
00:49:45.691 --> 00:49:49.045
by pirates. and dragons.
and storms. and then what?

597
00:49:49.069 --> 00:49:51.381
Eating dates and incense while Westeros

598
00:49:51.405 --> 00:49:53.925
-is reduced to ash?
-His Grace is in no state to fight.

599
00:49:53.949 --> 00:49:55.701
Neither would he tolerate
the Braavosi heat.

600
00:49:56.785 --> 00:49:59.055
-The monkeys alone...
-You surprise me. Lannister.

601
00:49:59.079 --> 00:50:00.682
Such a distaste for the foreign.

602
00:50:00.706 --> 00:50:04.019
I have lived with these people.
Do you forget? I've eaten with them.

603
00:50:04.043 --> 00:50:06.403
fought with them. shared everything
with them. even their...

604
00:50:08.088 --> 00:50:09.298
Yes?

605
00:50:10.299 --> 00:50:11.509
I know what they are.

606
00:50:13.511 --> 00:50:15.739
In Braavos.
I have prepared the means for us

607
00:50:15.763 --> 00:50:17.991
to live in a manner as befits His Grace.

608
00:50:18.015 --> 00:50:19.784
-We can ascertain...
-He is the king. Larys.

609
00:50:19.808 --> 00:50:22.787
Not some chip for you to hold
until such time as benefits you.

610
00:50:22.811 --> 00:50:25.207
-I have men riding with me...
-Sellswords.

611
00:50:25.231 --> 00:50:26.708
Cheaply bought. by the look of them.

612
00:50:26.732 --> 00:50:30.378
We need only bring him to Lannisport.
where he will be sheltered.

613
00:50:30.402 --> 00:50:32.797
From there. we may summon and command
what strength remains to us.

614
00:50:32.821 --> 00:50:34.508
Yes. no doubt it would be
the making of the Lannisters

615
00:50:34.532 --> 00:50:36.801
to declare Casterly Rock
the new seat of the king.

616
00:50:36.825 --> 00:50:38.345
Do you think even now
of your own advancement?

617
00:50:38.369 --> 00:50:41.348
Oh. begging your pardon.
most selfless of servants.

618
00:50:41.372 --> 00:50:43.225
I was only risking my life
at sea for our common cause.

619
00:50:43.249 --> 00:50:44.935
Gregor. is it?

620
00:50:44.959 --> 00:50:47.559
It seems I missed the salient moment
when His Grace made you Hand.

621
00:50:53.050 --> 00:50:56.136
You may call me "Your Grace."

622
00:51:08.649 --> 00:51:12.045
There is an evil spirit afoot.
This is no man. I tell you.

623
00:51:12.069 --> 00:51:14.756
Do not shame yourself. Ned.
We're knights. not infants.

624
00:51:14.780 --> 00:51:19.010
But we will find these cravens
and make a grim example of them.

625
00:51:19.034 --> 00:51:21.930
We are hunters. Not prey.

626
00:51:21.954 --> 00:51:24.915
-Hunters get paid.
-It's not safe out there!

627
00:51:27.418 --> 00:51:28.669
Enough.

628
00:51:30.004 --> 00:51:31.773
You and I are the protectors and keepers

629
00:51:31.797 --> 00:51:34.174
of the greatest Citadel
in all of Westeros.

630
00:51:35.676 --> 00:51:37.636
The governing seat of a mighty realm.

631
00:51:40.931 --> 00:51:44.101
Without the City Watch. without us...

632
00:51:46.478 --> 00:51:48.678
these streets would echo
with the cries of insurrection.

633
00:51:51.025 --> 00:51:54.462
The alleys of King's Landing would boil
with corruption and depravity.

634
00:51:54.486 --> 00:51:58.925
I look to you now to uphold your vows
to the city and to the throne.

635
00:51:58.949 --> 00:52:03.513
Trust in your queen. and I pledge you.
you will be repaid twice over

636
00:52:03.537 --> 00:52:05.581
for the sacrifices you make now.

637
00:52:08.292 --> 00:52:11.837
And in the years to come.
as Dorne finally bends the knee...

638
00:52:14.048 --> 00:52:15.734
as Rhaenyra's great empire grows

639
00:52:15.758 --> 00:52:18.153
and the Seven Kingdoms become Nine.

640
00:52:18.177 --> 00:52:21.472
become Twelve. become the new Valyria.

641
00:52:22.640 --> 00:52:26.202
When I return with wagons
spilling over with silks and silver.

642
00:52:26.226 --> 00:52:28.145
who will be the first...

643
00:52:29.480 --> 00:52:31.958
to celebrate in the spoils of conquest?

644
00:52:31.982 --> 00:52:33.233
We will!

645
00:52:34.360 --> 00:52:35.920
Groups of three and four!

646
00:52:35.944 --> 00:52:38.048
No man walks alone.

647
00:52:38.072 --> 00:52:41.492
Woodgard. Owtram.
you oversee the market square.

648
00:52:44.411 --> 00:52:47.641
It seems the Lord of Flea Bottom
has not been altogether forgotten.

649
00:52:47.665 --> 00:52:49.851
We've apprehended someone. Your Grace.

650
00:52:49.875 --> 00:52:51.210
At River Row.

651
00:52:51.835 --> 00:52:53.796
Then he will be the first to be repaid.

652
00:52:56.006 --> 00:52:57.776
Fall in!

653
00:52:57.800 --> 00:52:59.760
Stoney Sept beyond the rise!

654
00:53:21.865 --> 00:53:23.283
What is it?

655
00:53:26.495 --> 00:53:28.122
The Rivermen have crossed.

656
00:53:29.623 --> 00:53:31.250
And burned the bridge behind them.

657
00:53:33.127 --> 00:53:35.713
We can no longer delay their march.

658
00:53:40.884 --> 00:53:42.219
So we failed.

659
00:54:17.963 --> 00:54:19.315
How many others?

660
00:54:19.339 --> 00:54:21.008
Who was with you?

661
00:54:24.803 --> 00:54:27.139
I was the only one. I swear it.

662
00:54:28.182 --> 00:54:31.161
-I acted alone.
-Under whose instruction?

663
00:54:31.185 --> 00:54:33.496
I never saw his face. I told you.

664
00:54:33.520 --> 00:54:34.980
The tongue or the eye?

665
00:54:38.942 --> 00:54:39.942
The eye.

666
00:54:41.361 --> 00:54:44.239
It was the king. he said! Please!

667
00:54:46.200 --> 00:54:48.511
He said it was the king's work
I was to be about.

668
00:54:48.535 --> 00:54:49.870
It was Aegon then.

669
00:54:51.872 --> 00:54:53.081
No.

670
00:54:54.833 --> 00:54:56.376
Look.

671
00:54:58.670 --> 00:55:00.172
In my boot.

672
00:55:05.093 --> 00:55:07.971
Compliments of
King Daeron Targaryen. he said.

673
00:55:09.097 --> 00:55:11.892
For killing traitors to his throne.

674
00:55:20.442 --> 00:55:23.529
No! No! Please!

675
00:55:28.534 --> 00:55:30.470
There's none who
may say that you did not give

676
00:55:30.494 --> 00:55:32.180
your best effort.

677
00:55:32.204 --> 00:55:36.083
Perhaps this is the best
we could have hoped for.

678
00:55:37.084 --> 00:55:41.129
We've made our mark and returned alive...

679
00:55:42.923 --> 00:55:44.424
to Tumbleton. perhaps...

680
00:55:45.926 --> 00:55:47.928
to find out what Ormund has planned.

681
00:55:50.556 --> 00:55:52.724
I thank you for your offer. Ser Gwayne.

682
00:55:54.977 --> 00:55:56.645
But my path is set before me.

683
00:55:58.647 --> 00:56:00.583
And what is...

684
00:56:00.607 --> 00:56:01.984
What is that path?

685
00:56:03.569 --> 00:56:05.195
We'll raft the river.

686
00:56:06.196 --> 00:56:07.656
Or swim it.

687
00:56:09.283 --> 00:56:11.660
It was one thing to obstruct them.
Ser Criston. but...

688
00:56:13.370 --> 00:56:15.664
you must see they've gained the advantage.

689
00:56:17.249 --> 00:56:18.560
What more can we do?

690
00:56:18.584 --> 00:56:20.252
We will join them...

691
00:56:21.336 --> 00:56:22.754
in battle.

692
00:56:23.755 --> 00:56:25.817
Face them head on.

693
00:56:25.841 --> 00:56:27.926
We have half the men that we set out with.

694
00:56:29.469 --> 00:56:31.722
There are 200 Rivermen
for every one of us.

695
00:56:32.764 --> 00:56:34.516
That... you...

696
00:56:35.267 --> 00:56:37.185
It would march us towards certain death.

697
00:56:52.159 --> 00:56:55.203
This was your goal. wasn't it?

698
00:56:56.580 --> 00:56:57.789
All along.

699
00:56:58.624 --> 00:57:00.792
Our fate was always assured. Ser Gwayne.

700
00:57:03.170 --> 00:57:05.088
When we set out. we were doomed...

701
00:57:06.048 --> 00:57:08.067
to death and defeat.

702
00:57:08.091 --> 00:57:10.677
I have offered you sanctuary.

703
00:57:11.845 --> 00:57:13.364
Or at least the hope of one.

704
00:57:13.388 --> 00:57:15.349
You have offered me service to your house.

705
00:57:17.935 --> 00:57:19.561
I am grateful.

706
00:57:22.356 --> 00:57:24.733
But I have been a servant all my life.

707
00:57:27.402 --> 00:57:28.987
To green or to black.

708
00:57:31.198 --> 00:57:33.492
I have defined myself by oaths...

709
00:57:34.910 --> 00:57:36.411
through unyielding devotion.

710
00:57:37.955 --> 00:57:40.999
And the highborn have made much of me
while it pleased them to do so.

711
00:57:45.212 --> 00:57:47.297
But I will not let them diminish me now.

712
00:57:50.550 --> 00:57:53.720
I will not return spurned...

713
00:57:55.347 --> 00:57:56.723
rejected.

714
00:57:59.351 --> 00:58:01.436
I am the realm's greatest warrior.

715
00:58:04.022 --> 00:58:05.691
And I will die as such.

716
00:58:08.026 --> 00:58:09.194
Clear-eyed.

717
00:58:10.612 --> 00:58:11.697
Unbent.

718
00:58:13.490 --> 00:58:14.908
Glorious in battle.

719
00:58:17.160 --> 00:58:20.122
And not in their service. finally.

720
00:58:22.165 --> 00:58:23.375
But in my own.

721
00:58:28.088 --> 00:58:29.881
And they will sing songs of it.

722
00:58:36.013 --> 00:58:38.056
And Queen Alicent herself will hear them.

723
00:58:46.606 --> 00:58:49.627
The plan is to rebuild
the fleet at Driftmark.

724
00:58:49.651 --> 00:58:51.629
but it will take time.

725
00:58:51.653 --> 00:58:53.447
The Velaryon resources are diminished.

726
00:58:54.573 --> 00:58:57.176
A condition with which
I am all too familiar.

727
00:58:57.200 --> 00:58:58.827
The king consort. Your Grace.

728
00:59:00.495 --> 00:59:01.997
My prince.

729
00:59:04.791 --> 00:59:06.752
The price of our humiliation.

730
00:59:10.005 --> 00:59:11.965
-What is this?
-Who is this.

731
00:59:13.383 --> 00:59:15.611
Young Daeron Targaryen.

732
00:59:15.635 --> 00:59:17.804
Ormund has declared him king.

733
00:59:20.265 --> 00:59:22.225
We should have burned them
when we had the chance.

734
00:59:32.402 --> 00:59:34.505
<i>We have endured much.</i>

735
00:59:34.529 --> 00:59:36.656
Suffered much.

736
00:59:37.616 --> 00:59:39.242
This I know.

737
00:59:41.578 --> 00:59:44.372
And though we languish now...

738
00:59:45.499 --> 00:59:46.750
in the darkness...

739
00:59:48.794 --> 00:59:50.712
we will not lose heart.

740
00:59:52.297 --> 00:59:53.965
Come to bed.

741
00:59:55.550 --> 00:59:56.927
She hears something.

742
01:00:02.891 --> 01:00:05.060
<i>The Seven watch over us even now.</i>

743
01:00:11.691 --> 01:00:13.151
Look.

744
01:00:19.699 --> 01:00:21.409
<i>Let the Maiden grant us vision.</i>

745
01:00:22.786 --> 01:00:24.621
<i>For the way ahead is blessed.</i>

746
01:00:32.671 --> 01:00:35.132
Let the Warrior lend us his sword

747
01:00:38.593 --> 01:00:40.595
that we do not falter in our resolve.

748
01:00:42.305 --> 01:00:43.890
And the Smith...

749
01:00:46.726 --> 01:00:48.061
Let's go.

750
01:00:49.604 --> 01:00:52.149
Let the Smith bless us with his strength.

751
01:00:54.818 --> 01:00:56.903
<i>The Crone lights our way.</i>

752
01:00:59.281 --> 01:01:01.741
<i>Ours is the path of righteousness.</i>

753
01:01:05.871 --> 01:01:06.955
Ser Luthor?

754
01:01:13.128 --> 01:01:14.689
Careful.

755
01:01:14.713 --> 01:01:16.506
<i>The Mother gives her comfort.</i>

756
01:01:17.674 --> 01:01:19.384
<i>The Father. his protection.</i>

757
